On Jun 25, 2012, at 4:07 AM, Mohamad Ali Rostami wrote:<br><br>&gt; I have an error since a week ago which it makes me crazy. :P<br>&gt; I have a OpenMP parallelized fortran (f90) program which I am going to parallelize some part of it, using MPI (OpenMPI).<br>&gt; When I want to compile the code with my new MPI code, I get this problem: <br>&gt; "Error: There is no specific subroutine for the generic 'mpi_init'", while the compilation has no problem<br>&gt; with the header "use mpi" and even it seems that it does not have any problems with the variables and parameters from<br>&gt; MPI and the problem is just with subroutines.<br><br>This *usually* means that you are calling the subroutine incorrectly (MPI_Init, in this case).&nbsp; The prototype for MPI_Init is:<br><br>subroutine MPI_Init(ierr)<br>&nbsp; integer, intent(out) :: ierr<br>end subroutine MPI_Init<br><br>Are you passing a writable integer parameter?<br><br>-- <br>Jeff Squyres<br><a
